			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				    More addendums:<BR>
<BR>
    1)  Once I hit 22 I went to East Karanas and soloed crag spiders until I hit 24 (also having a partner helps if you think soloing here too risky).  You could get experience from crags until 26 if you want to stay that long.  Of course, there are lots of possibilities in South Karanas at these levels too.  I stayed away from aviaks just because there are a lot of newbie-minded folks trying to learn how to group successfully, and lots of trains.<BR>
<BR>
    2)  From level 24 until mid 30's, I camped the gnolls outside of Paw a lot.  The spawns are very consistent and the drops are very good (gnoll hide lariats make great pet weapons after level 34).  You can solo them as early as level 29, but I wouldn't recommend it.  This is a very group-friendly area until 34, when you can solo very successfully.<BR>
<BR>
    I hope these comments help enhance the usefulness of this guide.
				</font>
			</td>

